			<p class="bodyText">
				<strong>2.6 - Five (or Six) Rules for Creating a Great Game Today</strong>
				<table border="1" width="100%" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" bgcolor="#DEDEDE">
					<tr>
						<td valign="top" class="tablefloating" colspan="2">Thursday, May 13, 11:30 AM - 1:00 PM&nbsp;</td>
					</tr>
					<tr>
						<td valign="top" class="tablefloating" colspan="2">Room 406AB&nbsp;</td>
					</tr>
					<tr>
						<td valign="top" class="tablefloating" colspan="2">What does it take to create a compelling, original, powerful product in the game space today? What are the essential elements and necessary criteria for creating games that entertain and sell? Listen in as our panel talks about the basics of intelligent game mechanics, balance, elements of good level design and gameplay; the goals of artificial intelligence, reward systems; and the importance of storytelling--about the modern rules of successful game design, rules that reflect the changing market for games and evolving game player. If there are rules to making a great game today (and most designers will say there are) this panel will know what they are.&nbsp;</td>
					</tr>
																				
					<tr>
						<td valign="top" width="18%" class="tablefloating">Moderator:</td>
